        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 3:17PM CDT until May 6 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Webster Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
North central De Soto Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
Southern Caddo Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
Central Bossier Parish in northwestern Louisiana...

* Until 400 PM CDT.

* At 316 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Karnack to near Deberry, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Haughton, Ferguson, Curtis, Spring Ridge, Fillmore, Mooringsport,
Cross Lake, Bodcau, Koran, Eastwood, Shreveport, Keithville, Ivan,
Dixie, Princeton, Greenwood, Taylortown, Elm Grove, Linton, and
Benton.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain alert for a possible tornado! Tornadoes can develop quickly
from severe thunderstorms. If you spot a tornado go at once into the
basement or small central room in a sturdy structure.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northwestern
Louisiana.</instruction>
